      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): dedupe terminal error replies",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Telegram users could receive two visible terminal error replies for one failed request when the runner reported duplicate final failure payloads, for example a specific timeout message followed by a generic fallback error.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change records terminal error delivery in Telegram lane-delivery state and suppresses later duplicate terminal final-error replies after one terminal error has already been delivered. Non-terminal tool warning payloads remain outside this suppression path so tool warnings can still be surfaced when appropriate.\n\nThe change is intentionally scoped to Telegram delivery behavior. It does not alter model execution, retry behavior, or non-Telegram channel delivery.\n\nAI-assisted: yes; the final patch was reviewed with focused local tests and type/lint checks.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTelegram users should see one clear terminal failure message instead of a timeout/error pair for the same failed request. This reduces noisy duplicate error replies while preserving the first meaningful failure message.\n\n## Evidence\n\nLocal verification on commit `2135ebd3f44b1d1a00b999e15e12a7613845a75c`:\n\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <3 changed files>` passed.\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` passed: 135 tests.\n- Targeted oxlint on the changed Telegram files passed with 0 warnings / 0 errors.\n- Extension test typecheck passed:\n  - `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo`\n- Extension prod typecheck passed:\n  - `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --noEmit`\n\nNative Telegram behavior proof is still required by repository policy; requesting a Mantis Telegram Desktop proof run in PR comments.\n",
